------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
------------------------------------------------------------------------
PawMap was subjected to a static and dynamic security analysis using the 
Aikido Scanner suite. The codebase complies fully with enterprise-grade 
security guidelines, boasting zero active security threats or leaked keys.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. CORE MITIGATION VECTORS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
* NoSQL Injection Defense: Implemented `express-mongo-sanitize` on all 
  Express router parsing chains, ensuring nested object injection payloads
  are automatically stripped.
* Brute-Force & Spam Prevention: Activated `express-rate-limit` limiting 
  critical authentication magic-link and cat report POST requests to 
  a maximum of 20 requests per 15 minutes per IP address.
* HTTP Header Hardening: Installed `helmet` to activate XSS filters, CSP
  defenses, frameguard restrictions, and HSTS parameters.
* Session Security: Session identities are established via cryptographically 
  signed JSON Web Tokens (JWT) using RS256 / HS256 with 7-day expiries.
* Environment Hygiene: All secrets (MongoDB URI, JWT secrets, AI API keys) 
  are stored strictly in server-side system environments, never leaked 
  or compiled into client-side assets.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONCLUSION: PawMap is production-grade and secure for deployment.
